fields.headline: Corrections and clarifications
fields.bodyText: • We said the Pontcysyllte aqueduct was a Victorian engineering feat. It was constructed between 1795 and 1808, meaning it was Georgian, not Victorian (Car-free and carefree, 18 May, page 2, Travel). • We understated Guildford’s unbeaten run in the Four Nations Chess League by two. They have not lost for 79 matches over eight seasons, including the final two games of 2011-12 (Guildford extend unbeaten run to 77 matches, 11 May, page 19, Sport). • Other recently corrected articles include: At home with Vincent Kompany: ‘Setbacks, racism – everything fed my fire’ Adults with eating disorders ‘face appalling NHS failings’ Prada announces it is to go fur-free
